race.description: Barmah Park Restaurant & Cellar Door Handicap
race.comment: TSITSIPAS (3) has battled to find the form that he showed as a young horse, but did look something like his best last time out when finishing fourth over 2600m at Cranbourne in a stronger field there nearly a fortnight ago. She slides back again in class and gets his chance to show something this time. On top. MERCANTE (7) did a bit too much early on with the blinkers on at Geelong last time out, and to keep battling to finish fourth was a good run considering the circumstances. The blinkers are back off again, and he won't be far away. WHISKY MOON (6) kept up a strong gallop when finishing runner-up here over 3040m 15 days ago. He won't lack fitness and is expected to figure in the finish again. HIGHLAND GLORY (11) has not won for some time, but has been placed in 10 of his 16 starts over this trip. He has his best draw in a while and is always worth including in all combinations. DISCOBAY (12) was an overdue winner of his penultimate start, and then was fourth at Colac. Include.
